commentary: Boult to de Kock, no run de Kock is in quite a bit of pain after getting hit on his left forearm. He was beaten for pace as the short of a length ball bounced and seamed into him from over the wicket, he tried to defend but the ball burst through his defences and crashed into his bottom hand. He dropped his bat immediately and walked away, taking off his glove and wincing. He's on his haunches now and the physio is having a look at the hand. He is going to continue batting

commentary: Southee to Amla, 2 runs what on earth has happened there? Another chance isn't attempted. Amla went after a Southee short ball and pulled, he got a top edge that went in the direction of fine leg. Vettori was on the boundary and he completely misjudged it. He did not run in at all. Did he think the ball was going to carry to him, or did he just not see it? In the end it fell about 15-20 metres short. Bizarre.

commentary: McClenaghan to de Kock, 1 run stunning fielding! But Guptill misses the direct hit at the bowler's end with de Kock stranded mid-pitch. De Kock pushed the ball firmly to backward point and tried to steal the single to the wrong fielder. Guptill dived to his left, collected the ball after it was almost past him and bounced up in a flash. He had all the time in the world to line up the throw, de Kock had given up. But Guptill missed. Bad call from de Kock

commentary: Southee to de Villiers, no run that's a high full toss and it's hit AB and caused him pain. New Zealand are appealing for lbw though but the umpire says not out. AB is dealing with the blow but in the meantime New Zealand have asked for a review. AB had tried to play a reverse pull but was surprised by the high full toss and hit just below the hip. The impact was just outside off stump though, so I think he will be okay.

commentary: Philander to Guptill, 2 runs what on earth! South Africa are dozing in the field. Guptill tried to short-arm pull a ball that wasn't too short and ended up playing too early. The ball lobbed off the top edge behind square leg. AB de Villiers ran back from square leg and Steyn ran in from short fine leg. In the end no one called for the catch and both gave half-hearted efforts. The ball fell between them. Someone should have just called for it and gone quickly.

He had lunged a long way forward to sweep and missed. This time he was hit in line with the stumps very low on the front pad by the googly. Was there a bottom edge? Gone.

commentary: Morkel to McClenaghan, no run an appeal for caught behind after McClenaghan attempts the scoop over the keeper and the ball lobs to de Kock. South Africa think it's all over but umpire Davis says not out. South Africa review right away and replays indicate that the ball might have grazed the thumb as McClenaghan got down low to get under the ball and scoop. The third umpire decides there's not enough evidence to overturn the decision and McClenaghan has a laugh before batting on ...
text: an appeal for caught behind after McClenaghan attempts the scoop over the keeper and the ball lobs to de Kock. South Africa think it's all over but umpire Davis says not out. South Africa review right away and replays indicate that the ball might have grazed the thumb as McClenaghan got down low to get under the ball and scoop. The third umpire decides there's not enough evidence to overturn the decision and McClenaghan has a laugh before batting on ...

commentary: Steyn to McClenaghan, 1 run McClenaghan clears his front foot and slogs a short of a length ball to wide long on, New Zealand have broken their record last wicket stand in ODIs two games in a row. Move over Trent Boult, McClenaghan has taken your spot with Ronchi.

commentary: Philander to McClenaghan, 1 run mis-timed towards mid-on for a single, McClenaghan ran the first hard wanting the second, but decided against it

commentary: Philander to Ronchi, OUT it's all over! South Africa have been kept in the field for much longer than they would have liked, but in the end it is a thumping victory for them. Ronchi will have to wait for his maiden hundred. He falls after slicing the ball over point but Faf was quick enough to run back and take a well-judged catch
